<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.impendingdisaster.com/titles.php">www.impendingdisaster.com/titles.php</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Now, I HAVE seen the list of Mage titles (by lvl) before, the Elementalist, Arch Mage, etc. BUT I ran across a different table too (the SECOND table in the above link) and I am wondering what it means.<br>
<br>
This table was not by lvl only but lvl AND AAXP points.  This is the list of Baron/Baroness, Sage, etc.<br>
<br>
My question(s) are the following...<br>
<br>
Obviously, I don't have to worry about the TITLE thing for a while, BUT as far as the AAXP points go...<br>
<br>
1.   WTF are they?<br>
<br>
2.   As a Mage do I need to start working on THOSE yet?<br>
<br>
3.    If I do NOT need to start paying attention to my AAXP points at this time, when DO I need to take those into consideration and start working ON them. <br>
<br>
---After lvl 10, when I have to get my body?<br>
<br>
---Like lvl 20 after I get my surname? <br>
<br>
---or not until AFTER lvl 51...the first lvl in those titles? <br>
<br>
<br>
---or JUST BEFORE I reach those lvl's (like around the high 40's lvl's)?<br>
<br>
4.  OR am I already working on those?  Is this one of my stats somewhere (I have seen lots of stats, but don't know what all of the initials for them stand for yet). <br>
<br>
 Granted, I don't *think* that this is something that I need to be concerned with right now...BUT I did not know (until a friend told me) that I was even supposed to put training points (thus raise those points on my own, throughout the game) in that Niola Impholder (sp?) lady.  I just wan't to make SURE, I don't want to get up to lvl 51 like two years from now and THEN realize that I SHOULD have been working on the AAXP for the last 30 lvl's or something, then have to backtrack bigtime.  Especially since there are so FEW points in there (which means they may take a LONG time to get each one).<br>
<br>
And while I am here…another thing!  HOW exactly do you USE the “Chipped Bone Rod” to LOCATE your body?  Do I just HAVE it in secondary and it leads me there, OR do I have to do a spell for it, or take it out and click on it, or what?  I got one (because I don’t want to lose my body after I get to lvl 10 soon) but I am not sure how it works.  It doesn’t SAY how to use it when you right click it, just what it is!<br>
