<br>
I'm pretty sure you can find the answer to your questions by using the search function<br>
<br>
/em Raz Mask Off<br>
<br>
The quick and dirty:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Titles gained for Levels</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Elementalist (level 51) ==&gt; Conjuror (level 55) ==&gt; Arch Mage (level 60) ==&gt; Arch Convoker (level 65)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Titles gained for AA points</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Baron(ess) (6 AA points spent) ==&gt; Master(Mistress) (18 AA points spent) ==&gt; Sage (Don't remember exact, something like 42ish AA points spent).<br>
<br>
You can only begin to work on AA exp at level 51. In game, hit the &quot;V&quot; key to view your AA skills and to set how much experience you want to put into AA exp. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=60465">Xerphanis</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Convoker</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilyana>Kilyana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/03 5:28:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Stuff</span><hr size=1> All the stuff regarding titles/aaxp etc you need not worry about until lvl 51. <br>
<br>
at lvl 51, two things happen:<br>
<br>
(1) you become an Elementalist instead of a magician. This is nothing more than a title to congratulate yourself that you made it to lvl 51. When you get to 55, you become a Conjurer, and at 60 an Arch Mage. All these are just titles.<br>
<br>
(2) your AAXP becomes enabled. AAXP is basically an alternative experience bar. You kill stuff as normal, but you can decide to split the experience gained between the normal experience bar (the one that you have seen fill up since lvl 1) and the newly-activated alternative experience bar. When the normal xp bar is filled, you'll go up a level as normal. When the aaxp bar is filled you'll get an aaxp point. AAXP points can be spent on special abilities to improve your character, such as making you run faster, regaining health/mana faster, using less mana for spells etc. When you have a set number of aaxp points you get a title before your name. 6 points will make you a Baroness, some more points (not sure how many) will make you a Mistress and even more make you a Sage. <br>
<br>
I promise you that by the time you hit 51 you'll know what are the best ones to pick. If there's one thing about EQ, it's that you'll absorb a whole heap of information really quickly <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Don't know about the chipped bone thing though. I've lost my body more times than I care to remember <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 515<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/03 5:46:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stuff</span><hr size=1> At level 51, you become an Elementalist. Basically (like it was said earlier) it's a way to congratulate yourself for making it that high level. Of course now a lot of people will suddenly mistake you as a Wizard. /boggle<br>
<br>
At 55, you become a Conjurer.<br>
<br>
At 60, an Arch Mage.<br>
<br>
Lastly, at 65 you become an Arch Convoker.<br>
<br>
Starting at level 51, you have the option to earn AA experience points instead of regular experience points.<br>
<br>
At 51, you gain access to General AA abilities. Once you train six points in General, you gain the title Baron(Baroness). This is also known as your <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>First Title (TM)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
At 55, you gain access to Archetype AA abilities. However before you can spend points in Archetype, you must first have your First Title. After spending twelve points in Archetype, you gain your <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Second Title (TM)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. For Mages, your second title is Master (Mistress).<br>
<br>
Once you hit 59 and have your second title, you gain access to Class-specific AA abilities. After spending twenty-four points in Class, you gain your <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Third Title (TM)</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, which for Mages is Sage.<br>
<br>
Most planar abilities require you to be level 61+ (some, like Host of the Elements, require you to be even higher). There are no additional titles for Planar abilities.<br>
<br>
What exactly ARE AA points? Think of them as enhancements to the class. For example, under the General category you have the ability to increase your innate run speed, increase your base INT, increase your base HP regeneration, etc. Under Archetype, casters gain the ability to cast critical nukes, gain more hp, increase innate mana regen, etc. Under Class, Mages gain the ability to use /pet hold, turn into an elemental, conserve malachite when summoning pets, decrease cast time on our summons, etc. Under Planar Abilities, most are simply enhancements over existing General/Archetype/Class AAs (further increase innate INT, further increase chance for critical nukes). Others are all new abilities (such as Host of the Elements <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
Usually its wisest to wait til level 60+ before working on AA. I would recommend getting Innate Run Speed 3 as soon as possible though. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A> at: 1/9/03 6:02:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xalmat@themagicianstower>Xalmat</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 516<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/03 5:49:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stuff</span><hr size=1> BTW, to use the chipped rod, target <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>yourself</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> first. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=draccaviir>Dracca Viir</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/staricon.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/03 5:59:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=32.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/apothokeri/DraccaPhoto2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stuff</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em><