<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1. WTF are they?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
As stated, AAXP, or Alternate Advancement Experiance is for those who have passed level 50 and want to gain power in another way besides just leveling.  If you look through the history of any of the main class boards, you will find much discussion about the relative strengths, weaknesses and balance issues of each.  /Mourn Manaburn.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>2. As a Mage do I need to start working on THOSE yet?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
No, not for a while yet.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>3. If I do NOT need to start paying attention to my AAXP points at this time, when DO I need to take those into consideration and start working ON them. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Just hit V on your keyboard the next time you log in, and you will see a description of what's available.  They can only be gained at level 51 and above, and each tier requires not only certain numbers of points in the lower tiers, but that you be of a certain level as well.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And while I am here…another thing! HOW exactly do you USE the “Chipped Bone Rod” to LOCATE your body? Do I just HAVE it in secondary and it leads me there, OR do I have to do a spell for it, or take it out and click on it, or what? I got one (because I don’t want to lose my body after I get to lvl 10 soon) but I am not sure how it works. It doesn’t SAY how to use it when you right click it, just what it is!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The Chipped Bone Rod, as well as any other item you may aquire that has a spell effect that's not activated either by being worn or in combat is activated by right clicking the item when equipped.  It varies by item wether or not it needs to be in your hand or just in your inventory, and they never work from inside a container. <br>
<br>
You can also create a Hotkey of the item by holding down your mouse on the slot it's in, and dropping it in your Hotkey bank.  If you Hotkey an item, you can use it simply by pushing the number key associated with that hotbox.<br>
<br>
The items now say  in their description how to activate them, Such as {Effect:Vellium Shards (combat)} on any vellium weapon, or {Effect:Fungal Regrowth (worn)} on a Fungi tunic, or {Effect:Enticement of Flame (casting time: 2 years)} on the Vellious Wizard robes.  The ones that say they have a casting time are the ones that need to be right clicked. I'm not sure about the Chipped Bone Rod specificaly, but I do know it has an instant cast time, so should say<br>
Effect:Locate Corpse (Casting Time:instant)<br>
Charges: 3<br>
<br>
As to how Locate Corpse Works....<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">1. Go to the zone with the body in it.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
------When you do this, you must be in the same zone as the corpse.  If you die in Crushbone, you won't find your body if you use the wand in Greater Faydark.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">2. Target the person who's corpse you wish to find</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
------If you do not do this, you will find the nearest corpse, be it a player, or a Sylvan Bat.  This has it's applications too, but that is beyond what you need to find your body.  This spell does not assume you want to find <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>your</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> corpse, just <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>a</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> corpse, so be sure to target yourself if your looking for your own body.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">3. Be ready to go to your corpse.</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
------By this I mean, if you need to do anything at all besides walk strait to your corpse, do it first.  No Looting, turning to see something, etc, or you will forget which direction your corpse is in an you will need another charge from the wand.  If your far across the zone, a difference of a few degrees will put you far off course.  On any given Corpse Recovery, you will probably need all 3 charges if your body is any real distance at all.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">4. Right-Click the wand</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
------When you click, you will be spun around to face the corpse, and will now have the corpse targeted.  Simply walk in the direction you now face.  If the Gods of EQ are good, your body is in plain sight and easy to see in a clear area and will be easy to find this way.  Often, you will have to turn around trees, go around rocks, mobs etc... and you will need another charge to re-orient yourself on your body--Keep in mind you have only 3 uses of each wand, and on a flegeling bank account this can get quite cumbersome.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">5. Appendix 1:/corpse command</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
------If the gods of EQ are feeling a bit on the pissy side this day, and they are often grouchy, then the corpse will be stuck <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>inside</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a tree, hillside, or wall and you will not be able to click on it.  For that matter, you won't see it either and will probably spend a few charges trying to triangulate it.  Eventually, after many castings, you admit your body is indeed in <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>That</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> tree, and you can get no closer to it, sometimes you will see a finger or toe sticking out.  In this case, if the body is yours, or someone who has given you permission with the /consent command, you can use the /corpse command to summon your body to you from no further than 50 EQ feet--Not very far at all, sure don't <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>look</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> like 50ft.  The corpse will appear at your feet, and you may loot or continue to use /corpse to drag the body as you choose.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">6. Appendix 2:/Loot Command</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
------This is for advanced Users, normally those who get the spell from their class- Necromancers, Bards, and Shadowknights, but you can do it with a wand too.  If your fighting a monster, and you kill it, sometimes it's body is stuck in a tree, wall, hill, whatever, and you can't loot it.  It is commonly believed that any mob thus un-looted and lost will be the one with the messed up loot tables, and on it's rotting and out-of-reach body there will be 2 million PP, and at least 2 pieces of God/Dragon loot.  To prevent the possibilty of this happening, get as close as you can to the mob's body, and use the wand <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>without</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> having a target.  You will now be facing the body, and have it targeted.  You can, if you are close enough, use the /loot command to loot the body.  You might have to jump and use this command at the same time if the mob is in a tree--or get a Levitate spell in some cases--but if you can Locate Corpse, you will rarely loose a mob body entirely.  To date, no god loot or truck loads of PP have been recovered this way, but it never hurts to be safe. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
 <p><br>
